Create an administrator-only data export and relationship audit module for the ReGen PEPT platform.

The goal is to:

1. analyze the current data structure and relationship model first
2. verify that products, protocols, and FAQs are correctly indexed and linked
3. create secure admin-only routines to export:
   - all products as JSON
   - all protocols as JSON
   - all FAQs as JSON

Do not start by building exports blindly.
Start with a structural audit.

==================================================
PRIMARY OBJECTIVE
==================================================

Build a back-office admin-only utility layer that can:

- inspect the current data model
- validate relational consistency
- identify missing or weak links
- export complete structured datasets in JSON format

This must support:

- Products
- Protocols
- FAQs

All exports must include all associated metadata and linked references.

==================================================
SECTION 1 — STRUCTURAL AUDIT FIRST
==================================================

Before implementing export routines, inspect the current schema, indexes, collections, and relationship logic.

Analyze how the following entities are currently stored and linked:

- products
- protocols
- FAQs
- product-to-FAQ mappings
- protocol-to-product relationships
- protocol-to-clinical-objective mappings
- protocol variants / tempos
- monitoring profiles
- clinical objectives
- categories / tags
- authorship / status / visibility fields

Deliver a relationship map showing:

- primary entities
- foreign keys or reference IDs
- array-based relationships
- denormalized fields
- duplicated content
- orphaned records
- inconsistent naming conventions
- missing indexes
- weak links that may break exports

==================================================
SECTION 2 — VALIDATE INDEX AND REFERENCE QUALITY
==================================================

Check whether the current indexing and reference model is strong enough for reliable export and future synchronization.

Specifically verify:

1. Products
- unique product ID
- SKU or internal code
- peptide name
- strength
- form
- category
- tags
- availability / active status
- linked FAQs
- linked protocols
- linked pricing / commercial metadata if applicable

2. Protocols
- unique protocol ID
- title
- objective
- variants / tempo
- duration
- compounds / products used
- linked monitoring profile
- linked FAQ or educational references
- status
- visibility
- authorship
- versioning
- clinical metadata

3. FAQs
- unique FAQ ID
- question
- answer
- type / category
- visibility
- linked products
- linked protocols
- global applicability flag if needed

Identify:
- orphan FAQs
- products with no FAQ linkage
- protocols with missing product references
- duplicated labels
- protocol records using text labels instead of stable IDs
- inconsistent product naming across collections

==================================================
SECTION 3 — PRODUCE A RELATIONSHIP REPORT
==================================================

Create an internal admin relationship report before building exports.

This report must summarize:

- which fields are acting as IDs
- which references are stable
- which relationships are missing
- which entities need normalization
- recommended index improvements
- recommended schema improvements before export

The report should clearly distinguish:

- usable relationships
- risky relationships
- missing relationships

==================================================
SECTION 4 — ADMIN-ONLY ACCESS CONTROL
==================================================

All export routines must be accessible only to administrator users.

Create a secure admin-only route or admin tools area.

Requirements:

- admin authentication required
- non-admin users cannot access
- route must not appear in public navigation
- export buttons must only render for admin role
- log each export action with timestamp and admin user ID if possible

Example admin tools section:

/admin/data-tools

==================================================
SECTION 5 — PRODUCT EXPORT ROUTINE
==================================================

Create an admin-only routine to export all products in JSON format.

The export must include all associated product information.

Each product record should include, where available:

- id
- name
- sku
- peptide_name
- strength
- form
- category
- tags
- short_description
- long_description
- analytical metadata
- storage metadata
- pricing metadata
- availability / active status
- source / vendor if available
- related FAQ IDs
- related FAQ objects (optional expanded export)
- related protocol IDs
- related protocol objects (optional expanded export)
- created_at
- updated_at
- status
- visibility

The export should support:

- raw export with IDs only
- expanded export with linked records embedded

Filename example:

products_export_YYYYMMDD_HHMM.json

