==================================================
SECTION 8 — EXPORT OPTIONS
==================================================

For each entity type, support export modes:

1. Raw
- lightweight
- references by ID only

2. Expanded
- includes linked associated records
- useful for backup / migration / analysis

3. Audit mode
- includes warnings when references are missing or broken

==================================================
SECTION 9 — JSON QUALITY REQUIREMENTS
==================================================

All JSON exports must be:

- valid JSON
- UTF-8 safe
- consistently structured
- stable in field ordering where possible
- suitable for re-import or analysis

Top-level structure example:

{
  "export_type": "products",
  "export_mode": "expanded",
  "generated_at": "ISO_TIMESTAMP",
  "record_count": 123,
  "warnings": [],
  "data": [...]
}

==================================================
SECTION 10 — RELATIONSHIP NORMALIZATION RECOMMENDATIONS
==================================================

If the audit identifies weaknesses, propose and optionally implement a normalization plan.

Typical fixes may include:

- replace label-based links with stable IDs
- create explicit mapping collections
- standardize product IDs across protocol and FAQ records
- create FAQ-to-product and FAQ-to-protocol mapping tables if not already present
- normalize protocol variants under parent protocol IDs
- add missing indexes for objective, peptide, category, status, and visibility

Do not silently change production data without reporting.
First produce a recommended migration plan.

